The paper discusses the submission and peer-review process used by the Second Workshop on Sustainable Software for Science, which is focused on software engineering for scientific applications (cs.SE). The workshop also covers topics related to cyberinfrastructure (cs.CY), digital libraries (cs.DL), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and programming languages (cs.PL), which are all relevant to the content of the paper.
